******
[8] Viet Nam
Date: Tue 21 Jan 2014
Source: Saigon Daily [edited]
http://www.saigon-gpdaily.com.vn/Health/2014/1/107739/


The Children Hospital No. 1 reported 24 infants admitted for measles on 20 Jan 2014. This is the highest reported case number in 5 years. Before December 2012, the hospital had received no cases for the disease in 5 years, said Head of Infection and Brain section Dr. Truong Huu Khanh. Over 100 children have been hospitalized for treatment since then. Patients suffer high fever, rash, and pneumonia. Up to 80 percent of children infected live in Ho Chi Minh City.

Medical workers are worried about the spread of the disease and increased hospitalisation. Almost 65 children were admitted to the Tropical Disease Hospital in Ho Chi Minh City for the disease since December 2013. The average number children infected at Children Hospital No. 2 are 5-10 a day. The disease is transmitted through the respiratory system, said Dr. Khanh. Most patients affected by the disease have never been vaccinated.

The doctor urges parents to vaccinate their children at 9-months-old while it is most effective.

