[10] USA (Oregon)
Date: 21 Jan 2014
Source: KGW.com [edited]
http://www.kgw.com/news/Measles-case-reported-in-Marion-County-241319061.html


Marion County health officials issued a health warning after a child with measles was treated in a Silverton Hospital and transferred to a Portland hospital, according to a newspaper report.

The Statesman-Journal reported that an adult in a Marion County home traveled outside the U.S. and upon return was the 1st in the family to show symptoms. The rest of the family soon experienced rashes and fevers, with one child being treated on 12 Jan 2014.

The newspaper reported that a child visiting from Ukraine a year ago was diagnosed with measles, and that was the 1st case in Marion County since 2000.

There is no reason to believe that the public is at risk, according to a health department statement referenced in the report.

