[13] Australia (Western Australia)
Date: Wed 22 Jan 2014
Source: Radio Australia [edited]
http://www.radioaustralia.net.au/international/radio/program/pacific-beat/tourists-may-be-to-blame-for-west-australian-measles-outbreak/1251788


Health authorities say they suspect increased foreign tourism to regional destinations to be behind a spike in measles cases in Western Australia.

There have been 14 cases of measles reported in the state since October 2013, significantly up on previous years. Doctors say there is a risk the disease could spread, especially because Western Australia's vaccination rate is so low.

